commitResults.messageBody: Implemented delete assignment with student index and assignment name.

Fixed the bug of deleting students not immediately rendered on the front
end.

There were two bugs that may be helpful in future development:

1. Deleting the assignment was done by iterating through the list, and
did not break the loop when the assignment was found and deleted. This
caused ConcurrentModificationException, which happens when iterating and
modifying the list at the same time.
2. Executing commands should always go through the ModelManager to make
modifications, instead of manipulating the models directly. Deleting
assignment logic was moved in UniqueStudentList and set the student
after the deletion. This fixed the rendering issue as UniqueStudentList
is linked to JavaFX through observable list.
